Daily menu of an obese child: not breakfast and dinner filled
Over one third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity at 5 per cent.
Obese children come in most families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It shows again the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obese children are fed at least twice as often as children in families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had eaten fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a chance."
In families of overweight children there is no custom of practicing sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and took part in the same nearly 900 primary education children from all over Czechia.
It was already the second edition of the "Obesity of Not a Chance" program, which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12 thousand children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
An adequate diet and well-exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obesity children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals per day according to the diet: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," she collected one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but with dinner wrapper
Experts warn that in healthy development, details are important, too, that they also have, for example, a fixed time for family breakfast.
In Czechia, however, only 23 per cent of schoolchildren eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one has its own breakfast.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households nothing gets lost.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study shows that among families of obese children, fried potatoes are consumed more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink sweet refreshments daily (70%).
In general, more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed do sports, but among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age, from the point of view of healthy nutrition, are far from ideal."
Among your favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments," the final report of the study warns.
As a main meal, the pasta takes the palm and follows closely the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject vegetable and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Change to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after completing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence," in many cases a significant change was made in favor of the principles of healthy eating," the results of the study are pointed to.
It calls attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and current water.
Children would also choose in the questionnaire the poultry meat and the fish for the main meal and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
