On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, try to advance a number of required rivals (the normal one in a classic race), then try to win time (timed classic duel) and then wait a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all of this, the police sometimes appear, which only makes things more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite fewer landscapes in the game than could be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The model of driving follows the traces of previous episodes.
