If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a career conceived with a lot of action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better between the games of competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, this is no longer the same as the collisions.
Of games like this cannot be expected to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, by making a very tight advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it's completely destroyed.
Thanks to the rest system, there are no big problems, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The refreshments are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get out of the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, there are only five receptacles available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's nothing but help in case something goes wrong, but it's not much to trust.
Sometimes, neither the re-reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
