What a pity it is, at the most tense times, to reduce the quality of the image and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the quality of the image continues is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please the majority of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each one of his father and his mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game only for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Fun is secure, but prepare because mistakes will hit you in your eyes with the force of some airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Terciopel Students".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Academic Festival.
During the same period, twenty corals will be presented from secondary and university centers.
The festival revolves around two concerts on 17 November.
"The Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, on the festival committee is the director Václav Hampl," said the organization leader, Jakub Čaloun.
The festival's entire summit is the free admission for all audiences to the high school choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 14 a.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
The "Terciopel Students" concert will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university choirs, including the choir of the Carolina University, will participate.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day in a dignified manner and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Third Revolution, but also to present coral music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the principal of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised performances of students and morning concerts.
More information can be found on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
