For the general public, IBM is the symbol of a technological revolution, a company that is perceived as present and, however, has been 100 years since its foundation.
The basis for this long-term approach was put by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has already coined the motto that many of the world's problems have solutions if people are willing to think.
His motto "Think!" became his stamp, around which the life of the giant future will be built (it was also the title of an internal journal that IBM began to publish in 1935).
