The Government of a large-scale Social Democratic/Democratic coalition that is in power in Austria has decided on Tuesday to include in the Constitution a "golden rule" budget to reduce the public deficit and thus to avoid a possible degradation of Austria's sovereign note by credit rating agencies (triple A).
