The arrangement adopted by the Austrian Government approaches the "German model", since Germany was the first European country to adopt such a "rule".
Prior to 2017, the structural public deficit should decrease annually by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) and, as of 2017, the structural public deficit of the federal state should not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while regional States and municipalities should present balanced budgets.
The objective is that, by 2020/2021, public debt will be reduced by 60% as set out in the Maastricht Treaty.
