The most powerful segment is that of contactless technology, which allows you to pay for common transportation or purchases simply by approaching a card to a reader.
This year will be sold worldwide 460 million cards with contactless chip, 320 million more than the previous year!
Its share should continue to increase in 2012 (expected 580 million units) and represent about 10 per cent of the global chip card market (6.925 million cards).
Europe, which has long been behind the Asia-Pacific region, is gaining ground in the non-contact payment sector.
About 26 million Visa bank cards already have this function, which is accepted in 75,000 pay terminals.
In France, its beginnings are more modest: 400,000 Visa cards are being used without contact.
But the large surfaces work on four.
