In order to put the top gear, however, it is necessary for banks to make them available to their customers.
"There are two large French establishments that have undertaken to spread systematically in the future, among their customers, bank cards equipped with the system without contact," says Gérard Nebouy, Director General of Visa Europe France.
Banks prove payment by mobile phone
But it is only a first step towards the means of payment of the future: mobile phone.
At present, there are few devices equipped with NFC (Near Field Communication) technology, which is essential for carrying out the transactions.
"They're falling back."
"But I should finally experience a real boom next year."
"We plan to sell between 80 and 120 million units worldwide in 2012," explains Marc Bertin, president of Eurosmart.
But the banks take the lead.
The agricultural credit bank announced yesterday the launch of a test between December and June in Caen.
The iPhones will be equipped with around 200 customers and collaborators with a fund that allows the payment without contact.
